{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"Pn4jty9CxKSvbfTSqLMj3","title":"HPC","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"from":{"fname":"Software","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":5,"offset":776},"end":{"line":34,"column":21,"offset":792},"indent":[]},"value":"Software.HPC"}],"anchors":{"monarch":{"type":"header","text":"Monarch","value":"monarch","line":12,"column":0},"batch-jobs":{"type":"header","text":"Batch Jobs","value":"batch-jobs","line":20,"column":0},"linux":{"type":"header","text":"Linux","value":"linux","line":24,"column":0},"submittingrunning-jobs":{"type":"header","text":"Submitting/running Jobs","value":"submittingrunning-jobs","line":28,"column":0}},"fname":"Software.HPC","updated":1637982167107,"created":1636428217183,"parent":"AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"94c16e1230d4b4c25891109c20c6eba4","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"hpc\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#hpc\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>HPC</h1>\n<p>Entire section dedicated to setting up HPC and how to interface with it.</p>\n<p>HPC typically has slower cores, but a very large number of threads. This makes it well suited for applications such as Monte Carlo Simulations.</p>\n<h2 id=\"monarch\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#monarch\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Monarch</h2>\n<p>access the filesystem directly with ssh:// login details, works best with linux file browsers.</p>\n<p>Other OSs are really finicky and just through hissy fits.</p>\n<p>KDE's Dolphin is also finicky with this for some reason.</p>\n<h2 id=\"batch-jobs\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#batch-jobs\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Batch Jobs</h2>\n<p>Monarch has a max job limit of 4999, not 5000 as the docs suggest.</p>\n<h2 id=\"linux\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#linux\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Linux</h2>\n<p>The HPC system runs a Linux session for you, once you tunnel in via ssh.</p>\n<h2 id=\"submittingrunning-jobs\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#submittingrunning-jobs\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Submitting/running Jobs</h2>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"backlinks\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#backlinks\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Backlinks</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR\">Software (vault)</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.han_tests_2015","alias":"@han_tests_2015","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":120,"offset":727},"end":{"line":21,"column":135,"offset":742},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.han_tests_2015"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021","alias":"@baltagi_estimating_2021","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":156,"offset":763},"end":{"line":21,"column":180,"offset":787},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1,"offset":2366},"end":{"line":50,"column":12,"offset":2377},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1,"offset